Description: smart file editor launcher
 Opens files in the appropriate editor based on their MIME type (detected
 via libmagic or the mimetypes stdlib) or file extension.
 .
 The editor mapping is fully configurable through TOML configuration files
 layered at three levels: system-wide (/etc/edit/config.toml), per-user
 (~/.config/edit/config.toml), and per-project (.edit.toml in the CWD).
 .
 Features include:
  * Accurate MIME detection via libmagic (python3-magic) with stdlib fallback
  * Explicit --mime TYPE override on the command line
  * MIME type takes precedence over extension (configurable)
  * Editor values support flags: "code --wait", "vim -R", etc.
  * --dry-run / --list for inspection without launching an editor
  * --map FILE to interactively update the editor mapping for a file
  * --install-alias to create an 'ed' shortcut without packaging conflicts
